---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="about" description="About Igor">
  <h1>about<span class="cursor"></span></h1>

  <div class="post-content">
    <p>
      I'm <strong>Igor</strong>. Engineer, founder, occasional mountaineer. Based in Amsterdam.
    </p>

    <p>
      I spent years at <strong>Adyen</strong> building data infrastructure and an ML inference platform
      (<a href="https://www.adyen.com/knowledge-hub/the-ai-behind-uplift" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alfred</a>)
      that serves models in the payment flow at p50=20ms. Before that, <strong>Miro</strong>, where I worked on
      platform engineering and making large-scale systems not fall over.
    </p>

    <p>
      Three startups — <strong>Engenai</strong> (AI-powered discovery, acquired by Finaya),
      <strong>Resurgo AI</strong> (AI SRE telemetry intelligence, didn't make it),
      and <strong>KingSpeech AI</strong> (speaking coach, 2016).
      One acquired, two piped to <code>/dev/null</code>.
    </p>

    <p>
      I also taught algorithms at university and Python for two years — turns out explaining
      things to students is great training for explaining things to LLMs.
    </p>

    <p>
      I care about well-engineered systems, clean abstractions, and teams that ship.
      When I'm not building software, I'm probably in the mountains somewhere.
    </p>

    <h2>what I write about</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AI agents, LLMs, and making them actually work in production</li>
      <li>Data engineering and platform architecture</li>
      <li>Startups — the ones that worked and the ones that burned</li>
      <li>The occasional bash one-liner I'm unreasonably proud of</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>elsewhere</h2>
    <div class="social-links" style="margin-top: 0;">
      <a href="https://github.com/wundervaflja" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/igor-lushchyk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin</a>
      <a href="https://x.com/devnullgor_ua" target="_blank" rel="noopener">twitter</a>
    </div>

    <h2>about the name</h2>
    <p>
      <code>/dev/null</code> — the Unix black hole where data goes to disappear.
      Most of my side projects end up there. This blog is an attempt to rescue
      a few thoughts before they vanish into the void.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
